      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>drained green lentils</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong>,<strong> creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 2 min until the creamed coconut has dissolved</p><p>Stir through the <strong>mango chutney </strong>– this is your <strong>cauliflower dhansak</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
